INSERT INTO `cve` VALUES (1143,'2018-01-01','A remote attacker could inject arbitrary code into a targeted user’s web browser to gain access to the affected device.',1212,1195,'CVE-2018-19615','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-19615','2019-03-18'),(1144,'2018-01-01','A remote attacker may be able to use a proxy to enable functionality that is typically available to those with administrative rights for the web application, allowing the attacker to bypass authentication. Once bypassed, the attacker could disrupt user settings and device configuration. ',1213,1196,'CVE-2018-19616','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-19616','2018-12-26'),(1145,'2019-01-01','Using a specially crafted URL, an attacker can bypass user authentication to cause the device to reboot, which may be used to cause a continual denial-of-service condition.',1214,1197,'CVE-2019-6551','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2019-6551','2019-02-28'),(1146,'2018-01-01','A stack-based buffer overflow may allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on embedded platforms via traffic on Port 2947/TCP or crafted JSON inputs. ',1215,1198,'CVE-2018-17937','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-17937','2019-03-13'),(1147,'2018-01-01','The application contains a cross-site scripting vulnerability where displays that reference AF elements and attributes containing JavaScript are affected. This vulnerability requires the ability of authorized AF users to store JavaScript in AF elements and attributes.',1216,1199,'CVE-2018-19006','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-19006','2019-04-08'),(1148,'2018-01-01','Specially crafted packets to Port 102/TCP could cause a denial-of-service condition in the affected products. A  manual restart is required to recover the EN100 module functionality of the affected devices. Successful exploitation requires an attacker with network access to send multiple packets to the affected products or modules. As a precondition, the IEC 61850-MMS communication needs to be activated on the affected products or modules. No user interaction or privileges are required to exploit the vulnerability. The vulnerability could allow a denial-of-service condition of the network functionality of the device, compromising the availability of the system.',1217,1200,'CVE-2018-16563','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-16563','2019-03-21'),(1149,'2018-01-01','A specially crafted IRP (I/O request packet) can cause the driver to return uninitialized memory, which may result in kernel memory disclosure.',1218,1201,'CVE-2018-3989','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3989','2019-02-05'),(1150,'2018-01-01','A specially crafted IRP (I/O request packet) can cause a buffer overflow resulting in kernel memory corruption, which may allow privilege escalation.',1219,1202,'CVE-2018-3990','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3990','2019-02-05'),(1151,'2018-01-01','A specially crafted TCP packet sent to Port 22347/TCP can cause a heap overflow, which may lead to remote code execution.',1220,1203,'CVE-2018-3991','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3991','2019-02-05'),(1152,'2018-01-01','3.2.1    IMPROPER INPUT VALIDATION CWE-20',1214,1204,'CVE-2018-16561','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-16561','2019-04-17'),(1153,'2018-01-01','A Bleichenbacher-style side channel vulnerability in TLS implementation in Intel Active Management Technology before v12.0.5 may allow an unauthenticated user to obtain the TLS session key via the network.',1222,1205,'CVE-2018-3616','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3616','2018-09-12'),(1154,'2018-01-01','Multiple buffer overflows in Intel AMT in Intel CSME firmware versions before 12.0.5 may allow a privileged user to execute arbitrary code with Intel AMT execution privilege via local access.',1223,1206,'CVE-2018-3657','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3657','2018-09-12'),(1155,'2018-01-01','Multiple memory leaks in Intel AMT in Intel CSME firmware versions before 12.0.5 may allow an unauthenticated user with Intel AMT provisioned to cause a partial denial-of-service condition via network access.',1224,1207,'CVE-2018-3658','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-3658','2018-09-12'),(1156,'2018-01-01','3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW',1225,1208,'CVE-2018-13808','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-13808','2019-04-17'),(1157,'2018-01-01','3.2.1    CLEARTEXT TRANSMISSION OF SENSITIVE INFORMATION CWE-319An attacker with network access to Port 23/TCP could extract internal communication data or cause a denial-of-service condition.CVE-2018-13808 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 9.1 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:H).',1212,1209,'CVE-2018-13809','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-13809','2019-04-17'),(1158,'2018-01-01','3.2.2    IMPROPER NEUTRALIZATION OF INPUT DURING WEB PAGE GENERATION (\'CROSS-SITE SCRIPTING\') CWE-79The integrated web server of the affected CP devices could allow cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks if unsuspecting users are tricked into following a malicious link.CVE-2018-13809 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 6.1 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N).',1227,1210,'CVE-2018-13810','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-13810','2019-04-17'),(1159,'2018-01-01','Specially crafted network packets sent to Ports 80/TCP or 443/TCP could allow an unauthenticated remote attacker to cause a denial-of-service condition on a web server.',1224,1211,'CVE-2018-13798','http://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2018-13798','2019-03-21'),(1160,'2018-01-01','3.2.1    IMPROPER INPUT VALIDATION CWE-20',1214,1212,'CVE-2018-11451'